description:
&lt;p&gt;Staff Nurse - Inpatient Unit (newly qualified or experienced)&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;£24,214-£28,186 per year (pro rata) (dependent on experience), plus shift enhancements (potentially an average of 15% on top of basic salary)&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;*Upon satisfactory completion of Preceptorship Programme, salary will increase to £28,186 per year, plus shift enhancements.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Flexible hours, 22.5 - 37.5 hours per week, to include shifts, weekends and nights. Family Friendly shifts also available: Twilight (8pm - midnight) and Morning (9am - 2pm)&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Permanent&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;Location: Bray, Maidenhead&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;These are exciting times for Thames Hospice. We have planning permission for a larger purpose built facility due for completion in 2020, whereby we will be developing and extending our existing services.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;At present we are looking to expand our number of RGN&#39;s. We are looking for a motivated and enthusiastic Staff Nurse to complement our team of qualified Nurses on the Inpatient Unit. We are a supportive team and provide high standards of nursing care to up to 17 patients.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Palliative care experience is desirable but not essential. The post requires the ability to work shifts which includes nights from time to time.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We welcome applications from newly qualified Nurses who would like to complete their preceptorship year at Thames Hospice. There is opportunity to develop professionally and we will provide clinical training to support your specialist care and symptom management skills. Please see our Staff Nurse Development Programme attached.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Visit our website and watch our video to find out what it&#39;s like being a Nurse at Thames Hospice.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For an informal discussion about the role, please contact Sarah Johnston, Head of Clinical Services on &lt;span style=&quot;text-decoration: underline;&quot;&gt;sarah.johnston@thameshospice.org.uk &lt;/span&gt;or 01753 848925.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This appointment is subject to an Enhanced Disclosure and Barring Service check, including Barred lists.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Interview date: To be confirmed&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Employee Benefits&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;•27 days annual leave plus bank holidays (pro rata for part time staff). Increases to 28 days after 5 years continuous service&lt;br /&gt;•Enhanced Maternity, Adoption, Paternity and Shared Parental Leave Pay&lt;br /&gt;•Occupational Sick Pay&lt;br /&gt;•Thames Hospice Contributory Pension Scheme&lt;br /&gt;•NHS Pension Scheme – option to maintain or restart membership if you have been a member in the last 12 months&lt;br /&gt;•Opportunities for training and personal development&lt;br /&gt;•Employee Assistance Programme&lt;br /&gt;•Eyesight tests (and a contribution towards the cost of glasses for designated DSE users only)&lt;br /&gt;•Employee Discount Scheme to save money on top high street and online retail brands&lt;br /&gt;•Death in Service Benefit&lt;br /&gt;•Schwartz Rounds – these are bi-monthly meetings when staff from across the organisation come together to support each other&lt;br /&gt;•An active Staff Forum body – we use this to help us communicate and consult with our staff&lt;/p&gt;
